# Growth Experiment Loop

When running a growth experiment:

1. Read `/growth/program.md` master loop
2. Pick **one** EXP from `/growth/backlog.md`
3. Hypothesis: "If we [change], then [segment] will [action], because [evidence]."
4. Branch: `growth/<loop>-<exp-id>-<slug>` (`npm run growth:branch`)
5. Smallest useful diff; max files per `/growth/loop-manifest.yml`
6. Run `npm run growth:qa`
7. **AI hard review** per `/growth/ai-review.md` — Bugbot on branch changes; fix all block findings
8. Write `growth/runs/...-ai-review.md`; run `npm run growth:validate-ai-review`
9. Score with `npm run growth:score` — keep if QGS ≥ 13 and brand_risk ≤ 1
10. Append `/growth/results.tsv` (never overwrite)
11. Run log: `/growth/runs/YYYY-MM-DD-<automation>-<exp>.md`
12. Open PR with ai-review link in body — stop

See `/growth/scorecard.md` for rubric.
